        "cooked": "<p>Signal spends a lot of money on sms verification requests.</p>\n<p>A lot of that money can be saved by using the rcs protocol.</p>\n<p>Rcs is still limited to phone numbers, but instead of sending messages over an often expensive sms connection and instead uses standard data link, just like signal itself.<br>\nItâ€™s compatible with both the google and the apple sms app.<br>\nThere are some limits to that compatibility, but you could correct for that by having the second attempt at sending default back to sms.</p>",
