        "created_at": "2025-11-24T21:28:31.890Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"xor_suggest\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"73129\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/x/9d8465/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> xor_suggest:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>My proposal is to send the verification codes with rcs.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>And I responded directly to that.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"xor_suggest\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"73129\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/x/9d8465/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> xor_suggest:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Just like although the signal app doesnâ€™t implement any sms it still currently gets authentication form sms.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>There was still cost and engineering effort involved to build it out. Twilio didnâ€™t flip a switch and, <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/magic_wand.png?v=14\" title=\":magic_wand:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":magic_wand:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/sparkles.png?v=14\" title=\":sparkles:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":sparkles:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> magically  Signal had an SMS 2FA service.</p>\n<p>Edit: 2FA codes via RCS is not cheaper. In fact, itâ€™s more expensive by up to 150%:</p>\n<p>Average cost range per SMS message: $0.007 - $0.09<br>\nAverage cost range per RCS message: $0.0075 - $0.03</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://www.plivo.com/blog/how-rcs-pricing-works/\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6565737286e587567248583f/67c5b8d13e929d0429679058_Black%20Icon%2032x32.svg\" class=\"site-icon\" alt=\"\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://www.plivo.com/blog/how-rcs-pricing-works/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">plivo.com</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/344;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/4/14cffb4beea8a19463225904362d7b96fa5b2237.webp\" class=\"thumbnail\" alt=\"\" data-dominant-color=\"AFBFC1\" width=\"690\" height=\"344\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.plivo.com/blog/how-rcs-pricing-works/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">RCS Pricing Guide 2025: How Business Messaging Costs Work</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Learn RCS pricing structures, calculate costs, and maximize ROI for your business messaging campaigns with Plivo.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>A bit ridiculous that sending a message containing 6 numbers could cost so much.</p>",
